  Reconciler overlap (4 files)

  reconciliation_engine.py, registry_filesystem_reconciler.py,
  file_id_reconciler.py, file_id_reconciler_2efb6c.py — all reconcile
  registry vs. filesystem state. Likely doing the same core loop.

  Watcher overlap (3 files)

  filesystem_watcher.py, watcher_daemon.py, dir_id_watcher.py — all
  monitor filesystem for ID drift.

  load_id_type_spec (3 files)

  generate_id_automation.py, generate_id_docs.py,
  generate_id_validators.py — all load the same spec and differ only in
  what they output. Could be one generator with a --target flag.

  ---
  Bottom line: The collection has ~3 categories of overlap:
  1. Hash-suffix dupes (8 pairs) — versioning artifacts, one should be
  deleted
  2. Generated-but-kept generators — validators + the script that
  generates them both exist
  3. Semantic near-dupes — multiple files doing reconciliation,
  watching, or component ID generation with slightly different scope
